The paper discusses recent approaches to question generation using modifications to a Seq2Seq architecture, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of reinforcement learning to optimise for a reward that is less tightly coupled to the training data is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of quality metrics, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
